<br>
As your statement about prisoners in the US, a lot of people are jailed up without bail until their trials because they have a high chance of being a killer or fleeing (these people have yet to be commited by a trial of their peers).  They get passed around, and treated like shit, and used like rag dolls... know why anyone doesnt care? Because these men are usually the scum of society, and they dont run crying to guards, because most the guards are indifferent and dont want to get involved if not too much shit happens (major riots). <br>
<br>
(I've talked to a lot of cops about what happens - most Cops just want to live, rather than get in the middle of dangerous stuff that could be avoided) - Im not saying the guards lay a bunch of men on top of each other or something to interrogate them for evidence, Im talking about the inmate on inmate violence <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>(Juan on Juan).</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
As for prisoners in Iraq, even if they were innocent civilians, how many of them were are the wrong place where they shouldnt be at the wrong time - after curfew or whatever to be picked up?  <br>
<br>
Being in a &quot;war zone&quot; you think they would be smart enough to stay out of trouble, unless they were up to something.  In Vietnam (something my dad and all my relatives fought in against the Viet Cong), they told me horrible stories of the VC using any kind of dirty tactic from using women, children and other methods to kill enemies.... You think there could be a possibility that one of these &quot;innocent civilians&quot; could be scouting - for when to have the next suicide bombing?<br>
<br>
Liberals think too idealistically... when you see these things happen first hand, you would arrest those people too if they looked suspicious if it meant possibly saving lives or saving your own.<br>
